<TITLE> Paulson says US taxpayers at risk in bailout plan </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 WASHINGTON, Sun Sep 21,(bdnews24.com/Reuters) - US Treasury Secretary Henry Paulson acknowledged on Sunday an emergency rescue plan aimed at stabilizing a financial system in freefall will cost taxpayers money, but argued that costs will not be as high the $700 billion limit of the package. "The taxpayer is at risk," he said on "Fox News Sunday" television program, but added, "It would be extraordinary circumstances, highly unlikely, that the cost will be anything like the amount you spend for the assets.
